    </div>
    <div class="chapter-body">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="lede">The Delta is not a delta in the geological sense — it's a floodplain, built up over centuries by the Mississippi River's habit of overflowing and depositing rich alluvial soil. That soil made the region one of the most productive cotton landscapes on earth, and also one of the poorest.</p>
        <p class="body-p">[Section: flood history — the 1927 flood and its aftermath, the levee system, how the river's engineering reshaped settlement patterns. Pair with participant quotes on what the land means to them today.]</p>
