    <div class="chapter-body">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="lede">Chinese laborers first arrived in the Delta during Reconstruction, recruited to work cotton fields alongside newly emancipated Black workers. Within a generation, most had left the fields to open small family grocery stores — often the only merchants willing to extend credit to Black customers after plantation commissaries closed.</p>
        <div class="markers-row">
          <div class="trail-marker">
